    names: 'Ame-no-Uzume-no-Mikoto (天宇受売命 in Kojiki, 天鈿女命 in Nihon Shoki, "the Heavenly-Striking-Woman" / "the Heavenly-Alarming-Female") · Sarume-no-Kimi (the ancestress of the Sarume hereditary priestess-clan of the imperial court) · the Dawn-Dancer · the Kami of Mirth · the Patron of Performing Arts',
